name: Knysna Woodpecker
rangeDescription: Coastal southern south africa (western cape eastward to far southern kwazulu-natal)
description: A furtive woodpecker with densely spotted underparts and face. The male has a reddish crown and moustache; the female has a faint dark moustache and dark crown marked red only toward the back of the head.

name: Opal-crowned Tanager
rangeDescription: Southeastern colombia to northern bolivia and western amazonian brazil
description: Blue-and-black tanager with a bright creamy-white crown and rump patches; otherwise deep blue with black patches from the tail to the head. Compared to the similar Opal-rumped Tanager, this species has a distinctive whitish crown and a blue (not reddish) belly; the latter can be helpful for identification from below as it moves through the canopy with mixed species tanager flocks.

name: Sooty Grassquit
rangeDescription: Colombia to venezuela, guyana, and eastern and southwestern brazil
description: Small nondescript finchlike bird found at humid forest edges and in shrubby and grassy areas. Males are sooty black with a gray bill.

name: Madagascar Harrier-Hawk
rangeDescription: Woodland and savanna of madagascar
description: Large gray raptor with black wings and tail. There is a single white band through the tail and bare skin around the face that is normally yellow but which can flush bright red.

name: Yellow-billed Giant-Honeyeater
rangeDescription: Fiji (taveuni and vanua levu)
description: A very large, robust honeyeater. Entirely drab grayish-olive, with yellowish wings and tail and a bright yellow bill and eye-ring.

name: Azure-shouldered Tanager
rangeDescription: Coastal southeastern brazil (minas gerais to rio grande do sul)
description: Large tanager with a strong bill. Pale blue overall with deep-blue patches on the wings.

name: Gray-legged Tinamou
rangeDescription: Tropical forest of east-central colombia to southern venezuela
description: Unobtrusive, poorly-known tinamou. Mostly rusty-colored with a scaly back and wings.

name: Pictorella Munia
rangeDescription: Northern australia (fitzroy river, western australia to northwestern queensland)
description: Small, grayish-brown bird with a scaly white bib, a dark black facial mask, buffy belly, and a gray bill. Juveniles very plain brown, with faint outline of adult's mask.

name: Pale-browed Tinamou
rangeDescription: Tropical forest of western ecuador to northwestern peru
description: Secretive chickenlike bird that walks on the ground inside forest. Very plump; looks tailless.

name: Unadorned Flycatcher
rangeDescription: East slope of andes of southern peru (cusco) to western bolivia
description: Dull, medium-sized flycatcher of montane forest. Greenish gray, with dull reddish wings that have weak reddish wing bars.

name: Tolima Dove
rangeDescription: Forest and edge of mid-elevations on east slope of central andes (caldas southward to huila) and west slope of eastern andes (cundinamarca) of colombia
description: Shy dove found only in Andean cloud forest in central Colombia. The dull reddish-purple color on neck and breast, gray crown, and pale eye separate it from the much more common and widespread White-tipped Dove.

name: Mottled Petrel
rangeDescription: Breeds stewart and snares islands, and southwestern south island (new zealand)
description: A medium-sized petrel with a distinctive dark patch on the belly. Slightly larger and heavier-bodied than Black-winged, Bonin, and Cook’s Petrels.

name: Rufous-throated Wren-Babbler
rangeDescription: Mountains of eastern nepal to sikkim, darjeeling, and bhutan
description: Tiny brown ball of a bird with a gray face, a scaled chest, and a bright orange throat. Like other wren-babblers, often remains well hidden in dense undergrowth.

name: Iiwi
rangeDescription: Ohia and mamane forest of main hawaiian islands
description: A bright red Hawaiian honeycreeper of high elevation native forests on Kauai, Maui, and Hawaii Island. Very rare on Oahu and Molokai.

name: Rameron Pigeon
rangeDescription: Ethiopia to eastern democratic republic of the congo, tanzania, and south africa; western angola
description: Big, dark pigeon with a gray head, and bright yellow feet, bill, and eye ring. Plain in flight.

name: Visayan Bulbul
rangeDescription: Central philippines (guimaras, masbate, panay, negros, ticao, and verde)
description: A medium-sized bird of lowland and montane forest and more open wooded areas in the west-central Philippines. Dark brown above with a grayish-brown streaked crown, a white belly, white under the base of the tail, and a warm reddish-brown throat and chest.

name: Black-faced Monarch
rangeDescription: Eastern australia (cooktown to northeastern victoria); winters to new guinea
description: A slim songbird with rather long tail and substantial bill. Gray above, rufous below, with gray head, black forehead and throat.

name: Grayish Eagle-Owl
rangeDescription: Senegambia to ethiopia, somalia, northern uganda, and northern kenya
description: A fairly large gray owl with small ear tufts. The eyes are dark brown.

name: White-throated Jay
rangeDescription: Oak-pine forest of southwestern mexico (southern guerrero and south-central oaxaca)
description: Small, beautifully patterned jay. Very local in humid evergreen and pine-evergreen forest of mountains; endemic to southwestern Mexico.

name: Red-eared Parrotfinch
rangeDescription: Southern philippines (mounts katanglad and apo, mindanao)
description: A small bird of montane forest and scrub on Mindanao. Usually forages on the ground for seeds.
